## System 2: Task Memory (MUST FOLLOW)

For every new feature or significant task:

1. Create folder: docs/tasks/{feature-name}/
2. Write {feature-name}.md BEFORE coding -- 3 sections:
   - ## Plan -- What to build (goals, approach, end state)
   - ## Context -- Why these decisions (alternatives, constraints)
   - ## Checklist -- Progress tracking (tasks with status)
3. Work on 1-2 tasks at a time, update Checklist after each
4. New session -> read task file first to resume context
5. If the file grows too long, split sections into separate files

**Checklist Tag Convention (pipeline owner tags):**

Tag checklist items by pipeline stage owner:

- No tag -> BUILD (feature-developer)
- `(E2E)` -> Step 4 (e2e-test-developer)
- `(UX)` -> Step 5 (ux-tester)

```
- [ ] Unit tests: API + component
- [ ] E2E tests: critical flows (E2E)
- [ ] UX polish: mobile responsive check (UX)
```

**Golden Rules:**

- Never start coding without a plan
- Never do more than 2 tasks without updating the checklist
- When conversation gets long, suggest new session with task file

