## Hook Block Response Protocol (Always Active)

Hooks are fail-open -- they pass silently on timeout. When blocked, fix the root cause instead of bypassing.

1. Identify which hook blocked using the `HOOK:` field in the error message
2. Analyze the block cause (missing field, sequence violation, authorization failure, etc.)
3. Fix the root cause and retry
4. If blocked by the same hook 2 consecutive times -> report to the chairman
5. Minimum timeout is 180 seconds -- shorter values disable enforcement

