## AI Self-Correction Principle

Agent runtime self-correction in 3 levels (`.ops/self-correction/` reference):

1. **Self-Score (Level A)** -- Score own output 0-100 before submission. <70 triggers auto-rework (max 2x).
2. **Lesson Learning (Level B)** -- Compare validator results with self-score. Delta >15 or CRITICAL finding generates a lesson. Recent lessons auto-injected next run.
3. **Evolution (Level C)** -- Same category mistake 3x triggers evolution item (CHRO reviews). Max 20 items, 60-day TTL if untriggered.

### Self-Score Enforcement Gate

1. **100/100** -> proceed normally
2. **Below 100** -> per-item judgment:
   - **Actual defect** (bug, omission, missing test) -> FIX: rework
   - **Legitimate trade-off** (technical constraint, equivalent outcome) -> JUSTIFY: document reason
   - **"Too hard, skipped"** -> FIX: make-it-work principle violation
3. FIX items present -> rework (max 2x)
4. **100 or all items JUSTIFIED** -> proceed to next stage
5. Reports missing Self-Score section -> rejected, resubmit required

